    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen the diagnostic floating window is already shown, \"]d\" will not show the new floating window.\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim -u repro.lua`\n2. Open a lua file with some diagnostics\n3. Use ']d' to go to the first diagnostic, the window will be shown\n\n <img width=\"1310\" height=\"524\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c6e40976-2695-4e0b-bb68-fbaa8f6df951\" />\n\n5. Use ']d' to go to the next diagnostic, the window will not be shown\n\n<img width=\"1310\" height=\"524\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4b3746e8-be6b-4cb4-9668-0261fbe20ef5\" />\n\n6. If we close the floating window before jumping to next one, the new floating window will be shown\n\n```lua\nvim.schedule(function()\n  local sev = vim.diagnostic.severity\n  vim.diagnostic.config({\n    jump = {\n      on_jump = function(diagnostic, bufnr)\n        if not diagnostic then return end\n        vim.diagnostic.open_float({ bufnr = bufnr, scope = 'cursor' })\n      end,\n    },\n    virtual_lines = { severity = { min = sev.WARN }, current_line = true },\n    severity_sort = true,\n    signs = {\n      text = {\n        [sev.ERROR] = '',\n        [sev.WARN] = '',\n        [sev.INFO] = '',\n        [sev.HINT] = '',\n      },\n    },\n  })\nend)\n-- enable lua_ls to get some diagnostic information\nvim.lsp.enable('lua_ls')\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe new floating window will be shown.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.13.0-dev-179+gb8a24bfadf\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nrepo",
